shared.utils

Interface IServer

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MockServer, ServerProxy

    public interface IServer
    Interface to be implemented by servers, i.e. MockServer, ServerProxy, Server. All methods from API to be implemented with differing functionality
    Author:
    Seth White

    • Method Detail

      • Login

        LoginResponse Login(UserCredentials credentials)
        This method takes in UserCredentials, which contain a username and password, and determine if the inputed username and password is a valid combination. A LoginResponse will be returned back.
        Parameters:
        credentials - Information containing username and password.
        Pre-Condition:
        Username is not null., Password is not null., If the passed­in (username, password) pair is valid, 1. The server returns an HTTP 200 success response with "Success" in the body. 2. The HTTP response headers set the catan.user cookie to contain the identity of the loggedÂ­in player.
        Post-Condition:
        If the passed-in credentials is valid, the server returns a success response with a cookie.

      • Register

        LoginResponse Register(UserCredentials credentials)
        This method will take UserCredentials and determine if the inputed username already exists. If not, a new user will be created using inputed data. A LoginResponse will be returned back.
        Parameters:
        credentials - Information containing username and password.
        Pre-Condition:
        username is not null., password is not null., The specified username is not already in use
        Post-Condition:
        If there is no existing user with the specified username, 1. A new user account has been created with the specified username and password. 2. The server returns an HTTP 200 success response with "Success" in the body 3. The HTTP response headers set the catan.user cookie to contain the identity of the logged­in player., If there is already an existing user with the specified name, or the operation fails for any other reason, 1. The server returns an HTTP 400 error response, and the body contains an error message.

      • getGameList

        GamesList getGameList()
        This method will get a list containing the current list of games stored within the server.
        Pre-Condition:
        none
        Post-Condition:
        If the operation succeeds, 1. The server returns an HTTP 200 success response. 2. The body contains a JSON array containing a list of objects that contain information about the server's games., If the operation fails, 1. The server returns an HTTP 400 error response, and the body contains an error message.

      • createGame

        GameSummary createGame(CreateGameParams params)
        This method will create a game using the inputed game parameters within the server. Following this creation, a game summary will be returned to the client.
        Parameters:
        params -
        Pre-Condition:
        name is not null, randomTiles, randomNumbers, and randomPorts contain valid boolean values.
        Post-Condition:
        If the operation succeeds, 1. A new game with the specified properties has been created 2. The server returns an HTTP 200 success response. 3. The body contains a JSON object describing the newly created game.

      • joinGame

        boolean joinGame(JoinGameParams params)
        This method will add a user to a game that requires a player. The client will be returned a boolean stating whether they have been successfully added or rejected from the game.
        Parameters:
        params -
        Pre-Condition:
        1. The user has previously logged in to the server (i.e., they have a valid catan.user HTTP cookie). 2. The player may join the game because 2.a They are already in the game, OR 2.b There is space in the game to add a new player 3. The specified game ID is valid 4. The specified color is valid (red, green, blue, yellow, puce, brown, white, purple, orange).
        Post-Condition:
        If the operation succeeds, 1. The server returns an HTTP 200 success response with â€œSuccessâ€� in the body. 2. The player is in the game with the specified color (i.e. calls to /games/list method will show the player in the game with the chosen color). 3. The server response includes the Set cookie response header setting the catan.game HTTP cookie., If the operation fails,1. The server returns an HTTP 400 error response, and the body contains an error message.

      • saveGame

        boolean saveGame(SaveParams params)
        This method will save the game parameters to the server. The client will be returned a boolean if the game was successfully saved. Prepares params to be sent over network, then sends them to server to save a game
        Pre-Condition:
        Game id is valid., Filename is not null or empty.
        Post-Condition:
        A valid boolean returned.

      • loadGame

        boolean loadGame(java.lang.String fileName)
        This method will take a filename and try and load the game matching the filename input. A boolean will be returned to the client stating whether the game was loaded.
        Pre-Condition:
        A saved game with the specified filename exists on the server.
        Post-Condition:
        A valid boolean returned.

      • getCurrentGame

        ClientModel getCurrentGame(int version)
        Prepares the version number to be sent to the server, then retrieves current game from the server if it's different than the current version.
        Pre-Condition:
        User has logged on and joined a game, and therefore has cookies., Version is a valid integer.
        Post-Condition:
        A valid ClientModel returned.

        Post-Condition:

        Post-Condition:

      • addAI

        boolean addAI(java.lang.String AIType)
        Prepares the AIType to the server, then sends it to server to create a new AI player.
        Pre-Condition:
        User has logged on and joined a game, and therefore has cookies., There is space in the game for another player., The AIType is a valid type returned by the getAITypes method.
        Post-Condition:
        A valid boolean returned.

      • changeLogLevel

        boolean changeLogLevel(LogLevels level)
        Prepares the log level to the server, then sends it to server to change the granularity of the log it keeps.
        Pre-Condition:
        Level is a valid LogLevel (SEVERE, WARNING, INFO, CONFIG, FINE, FINER, FINEST).
        Post-Condition:
        A valid boolean returned.

      • poll

        ClientModel poll()
        This method will send a signal to the server checking to see if the current version of the model has been changed.
        Pre-Condition:
        none
        Post-Condition:
        Gets an updated version of the model from the server.

      • sendChat

        ClientModel sendChat(java.lang.String content)
        This method sends a chat message to the server. A new ClientModel is returned to the client.
        Parameters:
        content -
        Pre-Condition:
        none
        Post-Condition:
        chat contains the player's message at the end

      • acceptTrade

        ClientModel acceptTrade(boolean willAccept)
        This method will send a response to the server for a trade offer given to the client. A new ClientModel will be returned.
        Parameters:
        willAccept -
        Pre-Condition:
        Current player has been offered a domestic trade, To accept the offered trade, current player has the required resources
        Post-Condition:
        If the current player accepted, the current player and the player who offered swap the specified resources, If the current player declined no resources are exchanged, The trade offer is removed

      • discardCards

        ClientModel discardCards(ResourceList discardedCards)
        This method will discard a set of cards from the client's hand.
        Parameters:
        discardedCards -
        Pre-Condition:
        The status of the client model is 'Discarding', The current player has over 7 cards, The current player has the cards the current player is choosing to discard.
        Post-Condition:
        Postconditions, The current player gives up the specified resources, If the current player is the last one to discard, the client model status changes to 'Robbing'

      • rollNumber

        ClientModel rollNumber(int number)
        This method will roll the dice for the client if current turn. Following the rolling of the dice, the cient's model will be updated.
        Parameters:
        number -
        Pre-Condition:
        It is the current player's turn, The client model's status is "Rolling"
        Post-Condition:
        The client model's status is now in "Discarding" or "Robbing" or "Playing"

      • buildRoad

        ClientModel buildRoad(boolean free,
                    EdgeLocation roadLocation)
        This method will build a road for the client. A new ClientModel will be returned to the client.
        Parameters:
        free -
        roadLocation -
        Pre-Condition:
        The road location is open, The road location is connected to another road owned by the player, The road location is not on water, The current player has the required resources (1 wood, 1 brick or 1 road), Setup round: Must be placed by settlement owned by the player with no adjacent road
        Post-Condition:
        The current player lost the resources required to build a road (1 wood, 1 brick and 1 road), The road is on the map at the specified location, If applicable, 'longest road' has been awarded to the player with the longest road

      • buildSettlement

        ClientModel buildSettlement(boolean free,
                          VertexLocation vertexLocation)
        This method will build a settlement for the client. A new ClientModel will be returned to the client.
        Parameters:
        free -
        vertexLocation -
        Pre-Condition:
        The settlement location is open The settlement location is not on water, The settlement location is connected to one of the current player's roads except during setup, The current player has the required resources (1 wood, 1 brick, 1 wheat, 1 sheep and 1 settlement), The settlement cannot be placed adjacent to another settlement

      • buildCity

        ClientModel buildCity(VertexLocation vertexLocation)
        This method will build a city for the client. A new ClientModel will be returned to the client. updates model, builds a city in specified location
        Pre-Condition:
        the city location is where you currently have a settlement, you have the required resources (2 wheat, 3 ore; 1 city)
        Post-Condition:
        you lost the resources required to build a city (2 wheat, 3 ore; 1 city), the city is on the map at the specified location, you got a settlement back

      • offerTrade

        ClientModel offerTrade(ResourceList offer,
                     int receiver)
        This method will offer a trade with another player. A new ClientModel will be returned to the client. displays to other player a trade offer
        Pre-Condition:
        you have the resources you are offering
        Post-Condition:
        the trade is offered to the other player (stored in the server model)

      • maritimeTrade

        ClientModel maritimeTrade(int ratio,
                        java.lang.String inputResource,
                        java.lang.String outputResource)
        This method will complete trade with a maritime port. A new ClientModel will be returned to the client. trades resource cards according to a certain ratio
        Pre-Condition:
        you have the resources you are giving, for ratios less than 4, you have the correct port for the trade
        Post-Condition:
        trade has been executed (offered resources are in the bank, and the requested resource has been received)

      • robPlayer

        ClientModel robPlayer(HexLocation location,
                    int victimIndex)
        This method will move the robber and steal from a specific victim. A new ClientModel will be returned to the client.
        Pre-Condition:
        robber is not being kept in the same location, if a player is being robbed, the player being robbed has resource cards
        Post-Condition:
        robber is in the new location, player being robbed (if any) gave you one of his resource cards (randomly selected)

      • finishTurn

        ClientModel finishTurn()
        This method will end the client's turn and start a new players turn. A new ClientModel will be returned to the client.
        Pre-Condition:
        none
        Post-Condition:
        cards in new dev card hand have been transferred to old dev card, it is the next player's turn

      • buyDevCard

        ClientModel buyDevCard()
        This method removes resource cards from player's in return for a development card. A new ClientModel will be returned to the client.
        Pre-Condition:
        player has the required resources, there is a development card left in the bank
        Post-Condition:
        player has a new development card, if it is monument card, add it to old devcard hand else, add it to new devcard hand

      • playSoldierCard

        ClientModel playSoldierCard(HexLocation location,
                          int victimIndex)
        This method will play a soldier card from a player's hand. A new ClientModel will be returned to the client.
        Pre-Condition:
        player has the specific card they want to play in their "old dev card hand", player hasn't played a dev card this turn, It's the player's turn, The current model status is "playing", The robber isn't being kept in the same place, The player to rob has cards (-1 if you can't rob anyone)
        Post-Condition:
        The robber is in the new location, The player to rob gives one random resource card to the player playing the soldier

      • playYearOfPlentyCard

        ClientModel playYearOfPlentyCard(java.lang.String resource1,
                               java.lang.String resource2)
        This method will play a year of plenty card from a player's hand. A new ClientModel will be returned to the client.
        Pre-Condition:
        player has the specific card they want to play in their "old dev card hand", player hasn't played a dev card this turn, It's the player's turn, The current model status is "playing", The two resources you specify are in the bank
        Post-Condition:
        Player gains the two resources specified

      • playRoadBuildingCard

        ClientModel playRoadBuildingCard(EdgeLocation spot1,
                               EdgeLocation spot2)
        This method will play a road building card from a player's hand. A new ClientModel will be returned to the client.
        Pre-Condition:
        player has the specific card they want to play in their "old dev card hand", player hasn't played a dev card this turn, It's the player's turn, The current model status is "playing", The first road location is connected to one of your roads, The second road location is connected to one of your roads on the previous location, Neither location is on water, Player has two roads
        Post-Condition:
        Player uses two roads, The map lists the roads correctly

      • playMonopolyCard

        ClientModel playMonopolyCard(java.lang.String resource)
        This method plays a monopoly card from the player's hand. A new ClientModel will be returned to the client.
        Pre-Condition:
        player has the specific card they want to play in their "old dev card hand", player hasn't played a dev card this turn, It's the player's turn, The current model status is "playing"
        Post-Condition:
        All other players lose the resource card type chosen, The player of the card gets an equal number of that resource type

      • playMonument

        ClientModel playMonument()
        This method plays a monument card from the player's hand. A new ClientModel will be returned to the client.
        Pre-Condition:
        none
        Post-Condition:
        current player gains a victory point
